items.title: 2024 Nobel Peace Prize LIVE: Terumi Tanaka accepts award on behalf of Nihon Hidankyo
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Terumi Tanaka accepts the 2024 Nobel Peace Prize in Oslo on behalf of Nihon Hidankyo, an organization of survivors of the Hiroshima and Nagasaki bombings that won this year's prize.

items.title: South Korean parliament passes bill to appoint special counsel to investigate president
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
South Korea' parliament on Tuesday passed a motion to appoint an independent special counsel to investigate President Yoon Suk Yeol and top government officials over the martial law introduction in the country earlier this month. Read more: https://bit.ly/4g8r3ny

items.title: Brushfire in Malibu prompts mandatory evacuations
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Firefighters were battling a three-alarm brushfire early Tuesday in Malibu, California, near Pepperdine University, prompting evacuations. L.A. County Fire Department officials estimated that at least 100 acres had been burned and structures were threatened, according to KTLA-TV.

items.title: Netanyahu testifies in court in a corruption trial
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu was set to take the stand on Tuesday in his long-running trial for alleged corruption. It is the first time an Israeli prime minister will take the stand as a criminal defendant, an embarrassing milestone for a leader who has tried to cultivate an image as a sophisticated and respected statesman. Read more: https://bit.ly/49sSpCk

items.title: Jay-Z says lawsuit accusing him of rape is part of an extortion attempt
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Jay-Z says a rape allegation made against him is part of an extortion attempt. A woman who previously sued Sean “Diddy” Combs, alleging she was raped at an awards show after-party in 2000 when she was 13, amended the lawsuit Sunday to include a new allegation that Jay-Z was also at the party and participated in the sexual assault.

items.title: Hundreds protest in New Delhi against reported attacks on Hindus in Bangladesh
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Hundreds of protesters rallied near the Bangladesh diplomatic mission in the Indian capital on Tuesday, pressing for an end to reported attacks on Hindus and other minorities in Bangladesh after former premier Sheikh Hasina fled into exile in India in August.
